<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Script on kugarocks</title><link>https://kugarocks.github.io/en/linux/script/</link><description>Recent content in Script on kugarocks</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><copyright>Copyright (c) 2020-2024 Thulite</copyright><lastBuildDate>Tue, 03 Sep 2024 20:00:00 +0800</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://kugarocks.github.io/en/linux/script/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Basic Syntax</title><link>https://kugarocks.github.io/en/linux/script/syntax/</link><pubDate>Fri, 30 Aug 2024 20:00:00 +0800</pubDate><guid>https://kugarocks.github.io/en/linux/script/syntax/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="shebang">Shebang&lt;/h2>




&lt;div class="expressive-code">
 &lt;figure class="frame not-content">
 &lt;figcaption class="header">
 &lt;span class="title">&lt;/span>
 &lt;/figcaption>
 &lt;div class="highlight" frame="none">&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="c1">#!/usr/bin/env bash&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>
 &lt;/figure>
&lt;/div>
&lt;h2 id="variable-assignment">Variable Assignment&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>No spaces are allowed around the &lt;code>=&lt;/code> sign.&lt;/p>




&lt;div class="expressive-code">
 &lt;figure class="frame not-content">
 &lt;figcaption class="header">
 &lt;span class="title">&lt;/span>
 &lt;/figcaption>
 &lt;div class="highlight" frame="none">&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="nv">name&lt;/span>&lt;span class="o">=&lt;/span>foo&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>
 &lt;/figure>
&lt;/div>
&lt;h2 id="double-quotes">Double Quotes&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>Can interpret variables.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Condition</title><link>https://kugarocks.github.io/en/linux/script/cond/</link><pubDate>Sat, 31 Aug 2024 20:00:00 +0800</pubDate><guid>https://kugarocks.github.io/en/linux/script/cond/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="if-statement">If Statement&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>If the exit code of &lt;code>command&lt;/code> is &lt;code>0&lt;/code>, then execute the content of &lt;code>then&lt;/code>.&lt;/p>




&lt;div class="expressive-code">
 &lt;figure class="frame not-content">
 &lt;figcaption class="header">
 &lt;span class="title">&lt;/span>
 &lt;/figcaption>
 &lt;div class="highlight" frame="none">&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="k">if&lt;/span> &lt;span class="nb">command&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="k">then&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl"> ...
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="k">fi&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>
 &lt;/figure>
&lt;/div>
&lt;p>Another form.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Loop</title><link>https://kugarocks.github.io/en/linux/script/loop/</link><pubDate>Fri, 30 Aug 2024 20:00:00 +0800</pubDate><guid>https://kugarocks.github.io/en/linux/script/loop/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="for-statement">For Statement&lt;/h2>




&lt;div class="expressive-code">
 &lt;figure class="frame not-content">
 &lt;figcaption class="header">
 &lt;span class="title">&lt;/span>
 &lt;/figcaption>
 &lt;div class="highlight" frame="none">&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="k">for&lt;/span> var in list
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="k">do&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl"> ...
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="k">done&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>
 &lt;/figure>
&lt;/div>
&lt;p>The &lt;code>var&lt;/code> variable can be normally used outside the loop body.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Input</title><link>https://kugarocks.github.io/en/linux/script/input/</link><pubDate>Sat, 31 Aug 2024 20:00:00 +0800</pubDate><guid>https://kugarocks.github.io/en/linux/script/input/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="positional-parameters">Positional Parameters&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>Positional Parameters, script positional parameters.&lt;/p>
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>&lt;code>$0&lt;/code>: script name, including path.&lt;/li>
&lt;li>&lt;code>$1&lt;/code>: the first argument, and so on.&lt;/li>
&lt;li>&lt;code>${10}&lt;/code>: arguments greater than 9 need to use curly braces.&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>




&lt;div class="expressive-code">
 &lt;figure class="frame not-content">
 &lt;figcaption class="header">
 &lt;span class="title">&lt;/span>
 &lt;/figcaption>
 &lt;div class="highlight" frame="none">&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="cp">#!/usr/bin/env bash
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="cp">&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="nb">echo&lt;/span> &lt;span class="nv">$0&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="nb">echo&lt;/span> &lt;span class="nv">$1&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>
 &lt;/figure>
&lt;/div>




&lt;div class="expressive-code">
 &lt;figure class="frame not-content">
 &lt;figcaption class="header">
 &lt;span class="title">&lt;/span>
 &lt;/figcaption>
 &lt;div class="highlight" frame="none">&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">./foo a&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>
 &lt;/figure>
&lt;/div>




&lt;div class="expressive-code">
 &lt;figure class="frame not-content">
 &lt;figcaption class="header">
 &lt;span class="title">&lt;/span>
 &lt;/figcaption>
 &lt;div class="highlight" frame="none">&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">./foo
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">a&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>
 &lt;/figure>
&lt;/div>
&lt;h2 id="basename">BASENAME&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>Can remove the script&amp;rsquo;s path, leaving only the name.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Output</title><link>https://kugarocks.github.io/en/linux/script/output/</link><pubDate>Sat, 31 Aug 2024 20:00:00 +0800</pubDate><guid>https://kugarocks.github.io/en/linux/script/output/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="standard-file-descriptors">Standard File Descriptors&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>Standard File Descriptors.&lt;/p>
&lt;table>
 &lt;thead>
 &lt;tr>
 &lt;th style="text-align: left">Name&lt;/th>
 &lt;th style="text-align: left">Number&lt;/th>
 &lt;th style="text-align: left">Description&lt;/th>
 &lt;/tr>
 &lt;/thead>
 &lt;tbody>
 &lt;tr>
 &lt;td style="text-align: left">STDIN&lt;/td>
 &lt;td style="text-align: left">0&lt;/td>
 &lt;td style="text-align: left">Standard Input&lt;/td>
 &lt;/tr>
 &lt;tr>
 &lt;td style="text-align: left">STDOUT&lt;/td>
 &lt;td style="text-align: left">1&lt;/td>
 &lt;td style="text-align: left">Standard Output&lt;/td>
 &lt;/tr>
 &lt;tr>
 &lt;td style="text-align: left">STDERR&lt;/td>
 &lt;td style="text-align: left">2&lt;/td>
 &lt;td style="text-align: left">Standard Error&lt;/td>
 &lt;/tr>
 &lt;/tbody>
&lt;/table>
&lt;h3 id="standard-input">Standard Input&lt;/h3>
&lt;p>The &lt;code>cat&lt;/code> command reads content from the standard input by default. If you run &lt;code>cat&lt;/code> without specifying a filename, it will wait for user input.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Signal</title><link>https://kugarocks.github.io/en/linux/script/signal/</link><pubDate>Mon, 02 Sep 2024 20:00:00 +0800</pubDate><guid>https://kugarocks.github.io/en/linux/script/signal/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="bash-shell">Bash Shell&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>By default, the Bash Shell ignores the &lt;code>SIGQUIT(3)&lt;/code> and &lt;code>SIGTERM(15)&lt;/code> signals,
so executing the following commands will not have any effect (&lt;code>$$&lt;/code> is the process ID of the current Shell).&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Function</title><link>https://kugarocks.github.io/en/linux/script/func/</link><pubDate>Mon, 02 Sep 2024 20:00:00 +0800</pubDate><guid>https://kugarocks.github.io/en/linux/script/func/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="creating-a-function">Creating a Function&lt;/h2>




&lt;div class="expressive-code">
 &lt;figure class="frame not-content">
 &lt;figcaption class="header">
 &lt;span class="title">&lt;/span>
 &lt;/figcaption>
 &lt;div class="highlight" frame="none">&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="k">function&lt;/span> name &lt;span class="o">{&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl"> commands
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="o">}&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>
 &lt;/figure>
&lt;/div>
&lt;p>or&lt;/p>




&lt;div class="expressive-code">
 &lt;figure class="frame not-content">
 &lt;figcaption class="header">
 &lt;span class="title">&lt;/span>
 &lt;/figcaption>
 &lt;div class="highlight" frame="none">&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">name&lt;span class="o">()&lt;/span> &lt;span class="o">{&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl"> commands
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="o">}&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>
 &lt;/figure>
&lt;/div>
&lt;h2 id="function-return-value">Function Return Value&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>There are multiple forms of return values.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Parameter Expansion</title><link>https://kugarocks.github.io/en/linux/script/param-exp/</link><pubDate>Mon, 02 Sep 2024 20:00:00 +0800</pubDate><guid>https://kugarocks.github.io/en/linux/script/param-exp/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="parameter-expansion">Parameter Expansion&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>In Bash, parameter expansion is a mechanism for manipulating and handling the contents of variables.
Through parameter expansion, you can get the value of a variable, modify the value of a variable, or provide a default value for an unset variable.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Special Parameters</title><link>https://kugarocks.github.io/en/linux/script/special-params/</link><pubDate>Fri, 30 Aug 2024 20:00:00 +0800</pubDate><guid>https://kugarocks.github.io/en/linux/script/special-params/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="parameters-">Parameters: $?&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>The exit code of the previous command or script, 0 for success, non-0 for failure.&lt;/p>




&lt;div class="expressive-code">
 &lt;figure class="frame not-content">
 &lt;figcaption class="header">
 &lt;span class="title">&lt;/span>
 &lt;/figcaption>
 &lt;div class="highlight" frame="none">&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">ls &lt;span class="m">404&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>
 &lt;/figure>
&lt;/div>




&lt;div class="expressive-code">
 &lt;figure class="frame not-content">
 &lt;figcaption class="header">
 &lt;span class="title">&lt;/span>
 &lt;/figcaption>
 &lt;div class="highlight" frame="none">&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="nb">echo&lt;/span> &lt;span class="nv">$?&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>
 &lt;/figure>
&lt;/div>
&lt;p>Will output 2, indicating failure. The return code can be specified in scripts using &lt;code>exit&lt;/code>.&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>